      <section id="trust-ledger">
        <div class="kicker">Core Concept</div>
        <h2>The Trust Ledger – what boards actually need</h2>
        <p>
          Technical teams already maintain logs, tickets, and documentation across multiple tools.
          Boards and regulators need something different: one clear ledger of a few critical decisions,
          written in human language.
        </p>
        <blockquote>
          <strong>Example entry:</strong><br>
          Decision: “Enable AI-based scoring for customer applications.”<br>
          Who: Head of Risk, Head of Product, Data Science Lead.<br>
          Data/Models: 5 years of historical applications, gradient-boosting model.<br>
          Safeguards: human review above a threshold, quarterly bias checks, retention limits.
        </blockquote>
        <div class="badge-row">
          <span class="badge">Decision traceability</span>
          <span class="badge">Accountability mapping</span>
          <span class="badge">Regulator-ready evidence</span>
          <span class="badge">Vendor-neutral layer</span>
        </div>
      </section>

